The paper deals with building correspondences across different modalities, specifically video and language, which is a problem commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper proposes an end-to-end approach for video captioning, which involves training both the encoder and decoder simultaneously, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
